      "message": "This is a pretty long time. In other places where I\u0027ve made commit-based metrics, I use the age of the first commit after X has happened. In other words, updateLastCommitAge would look something like this:\n\nfunc (s *StatusWatcher) updateLastCommitAge() {\n\tst :\u003d s.GetStatus()\n\tif st \u003d\u003d nil {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tif st.LastCommit \u003d\u003d nil {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tcommitsFromLast :\u003d s.storages.VCS.Range(time.Unix(st.LastCommit.CommitTime, 0), time.Now())\n\tuningestedCommitAgeMetric :\u003d metrics2.GetInt64Metric(\"gold_uningested_commit_age_s\")\n\tif len(commitsFromLast) \u003c\u003d 1 {\n\t\tuningestedCommitAgeMetric.Update(0)\n\t} else {\n\t\tuningestedCommitAgeMetric.Update(time.Now().Unix() - commitsFromLast[1])\n\t}\n}",
